urls.title: Liquidity and Interest Rates on ERC-20 Fungible Tokens
urls.description: The liquidity of the the ParaSpace protocol represents the availability of capital to support borrowing amounts and redeeming nTokens and pTokens. The liquidity of the protocol can be measured via the utilization rate, which is the share of reserve that is currently borrowed for each asset. Interest rates are charged to borrowers based on the Utilization Rate, U U U. At a high level, the interest model helps incentivize what is needed to support liquidity.
